<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Expressly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Expressly,</orth> 1) in direct terms: <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.307" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 307</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 123.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.235" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 235</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 32</bibl>.<lb />2) expressively, distinctly: <cit><quote>their face their manners most e. told,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1397" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1397</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>who in his circumstance e. proves that no man is the lord of any thing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 114</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>